            I wish to ask two questions. If a private-sector auditor were appointed under the basic appointment provisions of Clause 14, would anyone who works on the audit&#x2014;from the most junior audit clerk to the most senior tax or IT partner&#x2014;have to be approved under those arrangements? My second question repeats what I asked in the introduction of the clause stand-part debate: does subsection (3) mean that all those people are treated as the auditor for the purpose of the access rights and therefore the ability to trigger a criminal sanction under Clause 18? I wish to be clear on those aspects.
